A US Navy sailor in the city for Fleet Week was punched in the face by a man claiming to be a Marine during a brawl on the Lower East Side early Sunday morning, police sources said. The 24-year-old seaman, who was in town from New Mexico, got into a fight with a man who told him he was a US Marine at the corner of Montgomery Street and South Street at around 2:30 a.m., according to the sources. The sailor was struck in the face and had his head pushed into the pavement, the sources said. He refused medical attention for a cut and returned to his ship. There were no immediate arrests. The sailor may have been intoxicated, a police source said. The Navy, Marine Corps and Coast Guard returned to the city for Fleet Week from May 25â€“31 for the first time in two years after the annual event was scuttled by the COVID-19 pandemic.